President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include Katharine G. Abraham as Chairperson of the Commission on Evidence-Based Policymaking, Rand Beers as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council, Diana Bolt Perreiah as a member of the National Infrastructure Advisory Council, W. Carl Lineberger as a member of the National Science Board, and Anneila I. Sargent as a member of the National Science Board. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their ability to tackle important challenges facing America.